Sentencas: Thin film solid oxide fuel cells (TF-SOFCs) having Ni-GDC anodes with different thicknesses of (1-5) mu m were fabricated on a nanoporous substrate termed anodic aluminum oxide (AAO) for low-temperature operation.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: By combining the co-sputtering method and the glancing angle deposition method, an ideal anode nanostructure with excellent porosity and electrical conductivity was successfully deposited.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The cell showed a high performance of 494.9 mW/cm2 at 500 degrees C having a three mu m thick anode.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: Proper balancing of electronic property and ionic property of the anode results in improved performance of 40.1% over the previously reported cells of similar architectures.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: Structural, chemical, and electrochemical analyses unveiled the correlation between the electrochemical performance and the anode thin film structure.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: In particular, the electronic and ionic characteristics of the anode were separated and intensively analyzed with the help of additional methods such as 4probe sheet resistance measurement and the distribution of relaxation time process with electrochemical impedance spectroscopy data.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: Through this, the influences of anode thin film thickness on electrical conductivity and fuel diffusion at the nanostructured anode and further on each resistance characteristic were identified, and its comprehensive understanding was gained.
Titulo: Effect of Ni-GDC anode thickness by Co-sputtering on the high-performance thin film solid oxide fuel cells on a nanoporous substrate for low-temperature operation
